# Salon 803 Application System - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit the .env file to version control

# ============================================
# REQUIRED - Google Apps Script Webhook
# ============================================
# The deployed web app URL from your Google Apps Script
# Get this after deploying the Apps Script as a web app
# Example: https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbz.../exec
VITE_APPS_SCRIPT_URL=your-apps-script-deployment-url

# ============================================
# REQUIRED - hCaptcha Configuration (Frontend)
# ============================================
# Get your site key from: https://dashboard.hcaptcha.com/
# This is the PUBLIC site key (safe to expose in frontend)
VITE_HCAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=your-hcaptcha-site-key

# ============================================
# Google Apps Script Setup Instructions
# ============================================
# 1. Go to script.google.com and create a new project
# 2. Copy the code from google-apps-script/Code.gs
# 3. Set up Script Properties (Project Settings > Script Properties):
#    - SHEET_ID: Your Google Sheet ID
#    - DRIVE_FOLDER_ID: Your Google Drive folder ID
#    - CAPTCHA_SECRET: Your hCaptcha secret key (from dashboard)
#    - PEPPER: Random string for IP hashing (generate with: openssl rand -base64 32)
#    - ALLOWED_ORIGIN: Your website URL (e.g., https://salon803.com)
#    - NOTIFY_EMAIL: (Optional) Email for notifications
# 4. Deploy as Web App:
#    - Click Deploy > New deployment
#    - Type: Web app
#    - Execute as: Me
#    - Who has access: Anyone
#    - Copy the deployment URL
# 5. Paste the deployment URL in VITE_APPS_SCRIPT_URL above
# 6. Create Google Sheet with worksheet named "applications" and these columns:
#    timestamp | name | email | phone | position | availability | experience | file_url | consent | ip_hash | user_agent
# 7. Create a private Google Drive folder for resumes

# ============================================
# Security Checklist
# ============================================
# ✅ .env is listed in .gitignore
# ✅ Apps Script PEPPER is at least 32 random characters
# ✅ Google Drive folder is private (not publicly shared)
# ✅ Apps Script ALLOWED_ORIGIN matches your production domain
# ✅ Different credentials for dev vs production
# ✅ Regular key rotation scheduled (see SECURITY.md)
